article_title: Aetna Tops Expectations for Affordable Care Act Membership
article_text:
Aetna Inc.’s enrollment in Affordable Care Act plans grew more than the company expected in the first quarter, but the insurer said it is still on track to roughly break even on the business this year, adding to the mixed signals from the industry about the direction of the health-law exchanges.

During an earnings call Thursday, during which the company reported better-than-projected results, Aetna Chief Executive Mark T. Bertolini said Aetna still saw its position in the ACA marketplaces as a “good investment.” But he...
